Hedione - derived from the Greek word 'hedone' - activates the pheromone receptor VN1R in humans . 
  This activates part of the brain responsible for triggering the release of sex hormones in women . 
  Christian Dior fragrance, Eau Sauvage , was the first to use Hedione in 1966 . 
  German study found it activated a specific hypothalamic region in women more strongly than in men . 
  Scientists analysed brain activity when a person smelled Hedione . 
 